      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HE IS THE KISS (7) finds the maiden win elusive (to say the least) but has been freshened with 59 days after finishing fifth over 1650m at Doomben in a tougher race. Best form is good enough so worth another chance. LUCKY ME (5) got a long way back before finishing sixth over a similar trip at Nowra last start, a less impressive effort than her fifth at Beaumont (Newcastle) the run before. Has been kept fresh for this and this looks easier, so can play a big role. AERIAL ARTIST (2) is a three-year-old gelding who is having his first run for the Adam Campton barn and gelded since last run. Resumes after finishing seventh at Gold Coast Poly at his last run five months ago. Ran fourth in a trial over 1000m at Gold Coast and looks well placed to make his presence felt. REVA'S CHOICE (9) disappointed last time but was good two back at Dalby when finishing in the frame. Can sneak a minor spot if on song.",
